# ðŸŽ¨ CompTIA Certification Color Guide

The colors used on the [CompTIA Certifications page](https://www.comptia.org/en-us/certifications/) are not decorativeâ€”they represent distinct career domains or specialization tracks. This visual taxonomy helps learners and organizations quickly identify certifications aligned with specific roles and skill sets.

---

## ðŸ”¹ Color Coding Breakdown

| Color Theme       | Career Domain / Track             | Example Certifications                     |
|-------------------|-----------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| ðŸ”µ Blue           | Core IT & Infrastructure          | ITF+, A+, Network+, Security+               |
| ðŸŸ£ Purple         | Cybersecurity                     | Security+, CySA+, CASP+, PenTest+          |
| ðŸŸ¢ Green          | Data & Analytics                  | Data+, DataSys+, DataX                      |
| ðŸŸ  Orange         | Cloud & Systems                   | Cloud+, CloudNetX, Server+, Linux+         |
| ðŸ”´ Red            | AI & Emerging Tech                | AI Essentials, Prompting Essentials        |
| ðŸŸ¡ Yellow         | Business & Digital Skills         | Project+, Business Essentials, Soft Skills |
| âš« Black / Gray   | Professional / Advanced Roles     | Ethical Hacker Pro, Security Architect     |

